{"editorCode":"; A geometrical model to multiply integers\n\n\n;Mary created the procedure \"rectangle\" that draws a rectangle (blue) with sides :x and :y \n\n; She also created the procedure \"rectangles\" that draws two rectangles, a blue one like the one described before and a red one with sides :n*:x and :n*:y\n; When she executed the procedure \"rectangles\" with positive and negative values at the parameters :n :x and :y, she made some conclusions  about the product's sign of numbers with the same or different sign.\n\n;Click the papyrus on the left to read the activity instructions.\n;---------------PROCEDURES-------------\n\nTo rectangle :x :y\nsetpencolor [0 0 255]\nrepeat 2[fd :x rt 90 fd :y rt 90]\nend\ncs\nrectangle 100 200 \n\n\nTo rectangles :n :x :y\nsetpencolor [0 0 255]\nrepeat 2[fd :x rt 90 \nfd :y rt 90]\nsetpencolor [255 0 0]\nrepeat 2[fd (:n*:x) rt 90 fd (:n*:y) rt 90]\nEND \ncs\nrectangles 2 30 40 \n\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.4283677494064476e-14,"z":233.2701559994168},"character":"Bird","notes":"Instructions\n-----------\nActivity 1\n---------------------------\nDefine and run the procedure \"rectangle 100 200\"\n\nTo define the procedure, select the lines from the word \"TO\" to the word \"END\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nTo run the procedure, click on the line \"rectangle 100 200\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nYou can enable the sliders tool by clicking on the trace in the scene. \nEnable the sliders and change the limits of the two sliders to -200 (min) and 200 (max)\n\nWhat sign should the parameters :x and :y have, so that the rectangle would be \na) right and up\nb) left and up\nc) right and down\nd) left and down\nThe terms right, left, up and down are referring to the initial and the final position of the bird.  \n\nActivity 2\n---------------------------\nDefine and run the procedure «rectangles 2 30 40». \na) Enable the sliders and change the slider limits of variable :n to 0 (min) and 4 (max) with step 0.1 \nDescribe what the bird draws and what is the role of each parameter.\nWhat is the relation between the red and the blue rectangles? \n\nb) Change the slider limits of variable :x to -60 (min) and 60 (max). Do the same for the slider of variable :y.\nIf :n is always a positive number, where would the red rectangle be for different values of :x and :y in relation to the initial position of the bird? Up and right, up and left, down and right or down and left? \nCheck your answer with the sliders.\n\nc)Change the slider limits of variable  :n to -4 (min) and 4 (max) with step 0.1.\nWhere is the red rectangle when :n has negative values and :x and :y positive values? \nCan you describe a conclusion about sign of the product of a negative and a positive number?\n\nd) i) If :n has always positive values, :x always negative values and :y always positive values, where would each rectangle be? \nCheck your answer with the sliders.\n  ii) If :n has always negative values, :x always negative values and :y always negative values , where would each rectangle be? \nCheck your answer with the sliders.\nCan you describe a conclusion about sign of the product of two negative numbers?\n\n\ne) Can you find all the cases (regarding the sign of the values of variables :n, :x and :y) for which the red rectangle would be up and left?\nDo the same for down and right , down and left and up and right.","sliders":{},"objects":[]}